@RickBullotta  @GeoffNunan @jh-isw  @Tor-Inge  Joining in on the discussion regarding a simple counter. 

This example is a very good reason for classic IT stream processing. How to store state? What happens during microservice / device restarts? How to ensure the system works in unbalanced scenarios (for some reason messages cannot be processed due to lack of CPU, ram, etc. and need to be queued)? When working with a lot of data points: how to do scale horizontally?

For this reasons we started to include Kafka in the United Manufacturing Hub as MQTT is not good at this type of stuff. At the beginning we were using MQTT and started to put more and more logic in our microservices doing this simple calculation until we landed up with couple of thousands of lines of code just covering most edge cases that might arise. And then we still had issues (local caches were failing due to hard device restarts, etc.) Couple of weeks ago we did the final switch and are now working with Kafka / benthos / mqtt-kafka-bridges, which allows engineers to write very simple equations without having to worry about "the weird IT stuff". We are also currently writing a blog article covering the reasons and the story behind it, will publish it here once it is finished.

